{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","author_sig":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","data":{"alias":"vanitied-kitschy-mammoth","creation_channel":"cli","description":"## Summary\nGraduate `src/rebar/llm/workflow/lint_refs.py` (currently 870 LOC, over the 800 soft cap and grandfathered on the module-size gate) off the allowlist by extracting the self-contained single-`${{ }}`-expression reference validator into a new pure-stdlib leaf `src/rebar/llm/workflow/lint_expr.py`. This is a pure/mechanical refactor: no behavior, signature, or logic changes.\n\n## Seam (existing call-graph cluster)\nMove the expression-grammar + expression-validation cluster — `_ID`, `_NAME`, `_ALLOWED_EXPR`, `ENGINE_INJECTED_INPUTS`, `_OutputContract`, `_Scope`, `_validate_expression` (~137 LOC) — into `lint_expr.py`. The leaf imports only stdlib (`re`, `dataclasses`, `collections.abc.Mapping`); ZERO rebar imports (a true leaf). `_output_fields_map` STAYS in lint_refs because it pulls the step-contract library (`.executor.contract_for`, `.steps`); the shared regexes/constants used by staying functions (`_EXPR_RE`, `_ENV_RE`, `_LITERAL_ONLY_FIELDS`, `_PLACEHOLDER`) STAY.\n\n## Back-compat\nlint_refs re-imports the moved names for its own internal use (`_OutputContract`, `_Scope`, `_validate_expression`) and re-exports `ENGINE_INJECTED_INPUTS` (added to `__all__`) — `lint.py:27` and `tests/unit/workflow/test_contracts.py:19` import it via lint_refs. `_Scope`/`_OutputContract`/`_validate_expression` have no external importers.\n\n## Deviation from docs/architecture.md\nThe offenders-table remedy row for `lint_refs.py` (docs/architecture.md, ~line 269) names a future `lint_contracts.py` seam and EXPLICITLY records that that seam is today SUB-FLOOR (the pure contract cluster is <100 LOC, below the 100-LOC leaf floor). This ticket does NOT take that stale seam; it takes the larger expression-validation seam (~137 LOC, inside [100,800]) which cleanly clears the floor. This ticket deletes that stale/superseded arch.md row.\n\n## Acceptance criteria (observable, in-session verifiable)\n- `wc -l src/rebar/llm/workflow/lint_expr.py` is in [100, 800].\n- `wc -l src/rebar/llm/workflow/lint_refs.py` is <= 800.\n- `lint_refs.py` removed from `.github/module-size-allowlist.txt` AND `.github/module-size-ceilings.txt`; its remedy row deleted from `docs/architecture.md`.\n- `python -m pytest tests/unit/test_module_size_contract.py -q` passes (allowlist == over-cap set == ceilings-keys stays consistent).\n- `python -m pytest tests/unit/workflow/test_contracts.py tests/unit/workflow/test_v2_ir.py tests/unit/workflow/test_editor_batch.py -q` passes (back-compat re-exports resolve; behavior unchanged).\n- `make lint` prints 'All checks passed!'.\n\n## Testing plan\nPure/mechanical refactor (symbol move + re-export; no signature/logic change) — E5 testing-plan is not-applicable; the existing tests are the oracle.","id":"2c35-394a-30b4-4b1d","parent_id":"716f-b917-9fc8-41f5","priority":1,"tags":["module-size"],"ticket_type":"story","title":"Split lint_refs.py — extract the ${{ }} expression validator into lint_expr.py"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1784397402479007001,"uuid":"7a1ed8f9-974a-4f3a-bd69-f90208fc08f9"}